cards.desc:
Currently we `cd dist; git init; git push --force $REPO master:gh-pages` to push our `/dist` directory from Travis CI to Github Pages (see `gulp deploy` task).  The problem with this approach is we loose our deployment history on the `gh-pages` branch (we also override the initial commit).

It looks like `git subtree push --prefix dist origin gh-pages` is the better approach, although from my understanding, it will mean the `dist` folder needs to be removed from `.gitignore` and will also live in the `master` branch as well as the `gh-pages` branch.

- https://gist.github.com/cobyism/4730490
- http://stevenclontz.com/blog/2014/05/08/git-subtree-push-for-deployment/
